## Subagent Dispatch

The main agent drives the FSM and reports progress between every state.
Only the proposer runs as a subagent (for context isolation of the asm +
history reading).

| State | Execution | Why |
|-------|-----------|-----|
| idle / gather / baseline | main | shell commands only |
| **analyze** | subagent (strategy-proposer) | reads asm + tile_config + history, emits tile_sizes proposal |
| implement | main | fill template literal, run divisibility gate, write file |
| compile_measure | main | shell: compile/profile/disassemble, IR dump, tail-loop grep |
| learn | main | record outcome, synthesize insight, decide |
| evaluate | main | restore_best, re-run, print summary |

### strategy-proposer subagent contract (recap)

- **Tools:** Read, Grep, Glob, Bash (only grep/head/wc/awk on .s, .json, .mlir)
- **MUST NOT:** edit files, run compile/benchmark, write .mlir, name
  transform-dialect ops, propose pipeline changes, propose
  custom codegen strategies
- **MUST:** cite specific asm lines, verify divisibility on the emitted
  proposal, output the JSON schema defined in `analyze`
- **Output:** one proposal object per call, OR `"no clear opportunity"`
  with justification

